Test auto.arima on simulated data¶

In [3]:
# Assuming 'forecast' package is installed and loaded
library(forecast)

# Simulate some time series data
set.seed(123)
ts_data <- ts(rnorm(100), frequency = 12, start = c(2000, 1))

# Simulate exogenous regressor data for model fitting
xreg_train <- matrix(rnorm(200), ncol = 2) # Two exogenous regressors

# Fit an ARIMA model with exogenous regressors
# fit <- auto.arima(ts_data, xreg = xreg_train)
fit <- auto.arima(ts_data, xreg = xreg_train)

# Simulate future values of the exogenous regressors for forecasting
xreg_future <- matrix(rnorm(24), ncol = 2) # Two exogenous regressors for 12 future periods

# Forecast using the model and future values of exogenous regressors
forecast_result <- forecast(fit, xreg = xreg_future)

# Plot the forecast
par(bg = 'white')
plot(forecast_result)

A single object matching ‘plot_auto_arima_forecast_fig’ was found
It was found in the following places
  package:AFTSCode
  namespace:AFTSCode
with value

function (da_ts, eotr, h, npts, frequency, xreg = NULL, gof = 36, 
    main = NULL, xlab = NULL, ylab = NULL, ylim = NULL, ts_fc_res = NULL, 
    ...) 
{
    if (is.null(ts_fc_res)) {
        if (is.null(xreg)) {
            tr_xreg <- NULL
            fc_xreg <- NULL
        }
        else {
            stopifnot(`xreg should be of type matrix and numeric` = (is.matrix(xreg) && 
                is.numeric(xreg)))
            stopifnot(`length(da_ts)!=dim(xreg)[1]` = (length(da_ts) == 
                dim(xreg)[1]))
            tr_xreg <- xreg[1:eotr]
            fc_xreg <- xreg[(eotr + 1):dim(xreg)[1]]
        }
        tr_da_ts <- ts(da_ts[1:eotr], frequency = frequency, 
            start = start(da_ts))
        if (is.null(xreg)) {
            ts_fm <- auto.arima(tr_da_ts, ...)
        }
        else {
            ts_fm <- auto.arima(tr_da_ts, xreg = tr_xreg, ...)
        }
        print(ts_fm$nobs)
        ts_fm$x <- tr_da_ts
        if (is.null(xreg)) {
            ts_fc_res <- forecast(ts_fm, h = h)
        }
        else {
            ts_fc_res <- forecast(ts_fm, h = h, xreg = fc_xreg)
        }
        par(bg = "white")
        tsdiag1(ts_fc_res$model, gof.lag = gof)
    }
    draw_arima_forecast_fig(da_ts, eotr, h, npts, frequency, 
        ts_fc_res, main, xlab, ylab, ylim)
    ts_fc_res
}
